The paper deals with the design of optimal linear codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The support constraint on the generator matrix is a combinatorial constraint, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the GM-MDS conjecture, which is a problem in coding theory and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Reed-Solomon codes is a common technique in coding theory and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the study of minimum distance, which is a fundamental concept in coding theory and network information theory (cs.NI).
